{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"assign","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:d"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tileLodZoomShift","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Shift applied to the Zoom level during LOD calculation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A negative value shifts the Zoom level to a coarser level reducing quality but improving","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"performance A positive value shifts the Zoom level to a finer level increasing details but","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"negatively affecting performance A value of zero (default) does not apply any shift to the Zoom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"level It is not recommended to change the default value unless performance is critical and the loss","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of quality is acceptable. A value of -1 reduces the number of displayed tiles by a factor of 4 on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"average It is recommended to first configure the pixelRatio before adjusting TileLodZoomShift.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnmapview\/tilelodzoomshift"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/tileLodZoomShift","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView